    <text id="A1401T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Ramsey writes from a prisoner of war camp in Maryland. He describes his health
                    and notes how he is comforted by his faith. He notes his wish to be among
                    friends and asks forgiveness for an unspecified action.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">"Maggie"</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-10-17">Monday <abbr expan="October">oct</abbr>: 17<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1864</date>
                        <name type="place"><orig reg="Prisoners'">Prisoners</orig> Camp, Point Lookout <abbr expan="Maryland">Md.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear Friend Maggie:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Though suffering this incarceration within the prison - walls of <abbr
                        expan="Point">Pt.</abbr> Lookout - <orig reg="though">thoug</orig> banished
                    from <unclear>friends</unclear> and <add hand="h1" place="inline">the society
                    of</add> much loved ones, I rejoice to feel the <orig reg="assurance"
                    >assureance</orig> that God is with us, and, we hope, will <hi rend="underline"
                        >turn</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">back</hi> our <hi rend="underline">captivity</hi> when we
                    are sufficiently humbled - that we may meet once more the kind - the sweet
                    embraces of our dear <hi rend="underline">relatives</hi>, and <hi
                        rend="underline">friends</hi>. But we would not forget the sweet words. "Not
                    very will but <hi rend="underline">thine</hi> be done. I wish I could be allowed
                    to write as much as I <orig reg="wished">wished</orig>. I could have much to say
                    to you - This privilege is denied me. But may be, you would ask Why is it that I
                    appear as willing to continue the correspondence which has <add hand="h1"
                        place="inline">been</add> so soon, and unexpectedly, cut short? I would
                    answer now, the same that I <hi rend="underline">would</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">have</hi> answered on that <hi rend="underline">ever</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">memorable morning</hi>, that it is as motive <hi
                        rend="underline">no</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">less</hi>, than a desire to cultivate the <hi
                        rend="underline">friendly</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">relations</hi> do not say, "there is none
                    <unclear>]</unclear> in existence between us. With <hi rend="underline">your</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">sanction</hi> our correspondence (though it will be rather
                    slow) will continue. I am pained when I think of my <hi rend="underline"
                    >uncivil</hi> conduct, when in your presence that morning, and also, those <hi
                        rend="underline">complicated</hi> mysteries that I had boldness to write
                        <unclear>since</unclear> at the expence of one so <hi rend="underline"
                        >truely innocent</hi> - Let me ask you to forgive me, and not only to
                    destroy these <hi rend="underline">letters</hi>, but even tho <hi
                        rend="underline">recollection</hi> of them <orig reg="forever">for
                    ever</orig>. I can write no more now. I will send you a stamp all I have. Brown
                    landed here a few days ago &amp; we both have slight colds, with that
                    exception we are <add hand="h1" place="inline">
                        <hi rend="underline">well</hi>
                    </add>
                    <orig reg="Inform">In form</orig> my mother that I have heard from <hi
                        rend="underline">Danville</hi> and <hi rend="underline">Mr. Kelso</hi> -
                    they are <hi rend="underline">well</hi> Their school is still going <del
                        hand="h1"/> Their children (<hi rend="underline">two</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">daughters</hi>) are well also.<pb n="2"/> Direct to <abbr
                        expan="Company">Co</abbr> "B" 2<hi rend="super">nd</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Division">Div</abbr> care of <hi rend="underline"><abbr
                            expan="Major">Maj.</abbr> Brady Provost <abbr expan="Master"
                    >Mas</abbr></hi></p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours &amp;c as ever</salute>
                    <signed>R. Y. Ramsey</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
